('msg-127', 'conv-001', 'assistant', 'AB-PMJAY package rates for diabetes management: Basic package (OPD management): Rs 15,000-20,000. Diabetes with complications (nephropathy, retinopathy): Rs 30,000-60,000. Diabetic foot management: Rs 30,000-60,000 depending on Wagner grade. Dialysis for diabetic nephropathy: Rs 12,000-15,000 per month (up to 12 sessions). These are package rates - actual reimbursement depends on the State Health Agency rates in Delhi. Always verify current rates on the SHA portal.', 'text', '{"references": ["AB-PMJAY HBP Master 2025"]}', '2026-03-15 09:27:00'),
('msg-128', 'conv-010', 'assistant', 'For WhatsApp Business API integration: AyushmanLife supports WhatsApp notifications through the official WhatsApp Business API. Setup requires: 1) WhatsApp Business account verification 2) API key configuration in Settings > Integrations > WhatsApp 3) Template message approval from WhatsApp for each notification type 4) Patient consent collection for WhatsApp communication. Contact the system administrator or raise a Service Desk ticket for API key setup assistance.', 'text', NULL, '2026-03-22 10:17:00'),
('msg-129', 'conv-012', 'assistant', 'Reminder set for INR recheck for Surinder Kaur on March 27. I have also added a clinical note about the papaya interaction in her medical record, and updated her Warfarin dose in the medication module to reflect the reduction from 5mg to 4mg daily. Diet counseling card for Warfarin patients has been printed.', 'text', NULL, '2026-03-23 09:32:00'),
('msg-130', 'conv-015', 'assistant', 'Appointment scheduled: Kamala Rani follow-up on May 6, 2026 at 10:00 AM with Dr. Amit Verma (Orthopedics). Referral to Endocrinology (Dr. Priya Patel) created for diabetes optimization. Pre-TKR checklist marked as pending glycemic optimization. System will auto-alert at 6 weeks for HbA1c recheck.', 'text', NULL, '2026-03-25 09:37:00'),
('msg-131', 'conv-009', 'assistant', 'High priority flag set for Ashok Pandey diabetic foot care. Vascular surgery referral created as urgent. AV assessment appointment available on March 25 with the visiting vascular surgeon. Wound care nurse notified for daily dressing changes. Orthotics consulted for offloading footwear.', 'text', NULL, '2026-03-21 09:32:00'),
('msg-132', 'conv-014', 'assistant', 'Summary for Tapan Mukherjee: Treatment plan updated to switch from Warfarin to Apixaban 5mg BD. Protocol: Stop Warfarin today, check INR tomorrow, start Apixaban when INR <2.5. No bridging needed. CGHS specialist prescription prepared. Follow-up renal function in 4 months. All documented in clinical notes.', 'text', NULL, '2026-03-24 10:50:00'),
('msg-133', 'conv-016', 'assistant', 'I can check the cold chain inventory for you. Based on the last stock update, PCV-13 stock is adequate for the current month. However, I recommend verifying directly through the Inventory module > Cold Chain > Vaccine Stock. For any shortages, raise a requisition through the standard procurement workflow.', 'text', NULL, '2026-03-25 14:27:00'),
('msg-134', 'conv-017', 'user', 'Good. Please also check if we need to update his AB-PMJAY package for the increased dialysis frequency.', 'text', NULL, '2026-03-26 09:38:00'),
('msg-135', 'conv-003', 'assistant', 'Medication reconciliation report generated for Arun Krishnan. Current active medications: Tiotropium 18mcg OD, Formoterol 12mcg BD, Budesonide 400mcg BD, Salbutamol PRN, Montelukast 10mg OD, Pantoprazole 40mg OD. Recommended changes flagged: Consider Roflumilast addition, inhaler technique reassessment scheduled. Report available in patient documents section.', 'text', NULL, '2026-03-17 11:32:00'),
('msg-136', 'conv-006', 'assistant', 'Exercise prescription form generated for Dinesh Tiwari. Includes: Phase II cardiac rehab protocol, 12-week progressive exercise plan, HR zone calculations (40-60% HRR = 88-106 bpm), safety parameters, emergency protocol. Form signed by Dr. Rajesh Sharma (Cardiology). Patient enrolled in cardiac rehab program starting April 1, 2026.', 'text', NULL, '2026-03-19 09:47:00'),
('msg-137', 'conv-019', 'assistant', 'RTA multiple injury coding: Primary: S72.301A (Fracture shaft of femur). Use S-codes for each injury with 7th character for encounter type (A=initial, D=subsequent, S=sequela). External cause: V89.2XXA (Motor vehicle accident). Place of occurrence: Y93.89. Add all injury codes in order of severity. For AB-PMJAY, the highest severity injury drives package selection for polytrauma (Rs 50,000-200,000).', 'text', NULL, '2026-03-27 10:37:00'),
('msg-138', 'conv-020', 'assistant', 'Complete medication plan has been documented in Meera Nambiar patient record. Prescriptions generated for Torsemide 10mg and Prazosin 0.5mg. Follow-up appointments set: Week 1 (phone), Week 2 (clinic), Week 4 (full review). ECHS prescription forwarded to pharmacy. Lab orders placed for RFT and electrolytes at 1 week. BP diary template printed for home monitoring.', 'text', NULL, '2026-03-28 09:40:00'),
('msg-139', 'conv-004', 'assistant', 'You are welcome. If you encounter any issues during resubmission, you can reach out again or raise a Service Desk ticket under category Claims > Resubmission for priority handling. Good luck with the processing.', 'text', NULL, '2026-03-18 09:52:00'),
