('msg-152', 'conv-005', 'assistant', 'Drug interaction check for Savitri Mishra completed. Current medications: Vildagliptin 50mg BD, Telmisartan 40mg OD, Amlodipine 5mg OD, Levothyroxine 50mcg OD, Calcium + Vitamin D3. Interaction alert: Calcium should be taken 4 hours apart from Levothyroxine (reduces absorption). No other significant interactions detected. Suggest taking Levothyroxine on empty stomach in morning, Calcium with lunch/dinner.', 'text', NULL, '2026-03-18 14:35:00'),
('msg-153', 'conv-002', 'user', 'Also, what is the risk of graft occlusion at 4 years post-CABG?', 'text', NULL, '2026-03-16 10:35:00'),
('msg-154', 'conv-002', 'assistant', 'Graft patency rates at 4 years post-CABG: Saphenous vein grafts (SVG): 80-85% patent at 5 years (15-20% occlusion risk). Left Internal Mammary Artery (LIMA) to LAD: 95-98% patent at 10 years (gold standard). Radial artery grafts: 85-90% patent at 5 years. For Suresh Babu, the EF decline from 45% to 38% raises concern for SVG occlusion. LIMA graft is likely still patent. Risk factors for early graft failure in his case: diabetes, dyslipidemia, hypertension. CT angiography will clarify graft status. If SVG occluded, options include PCI to native vessel or redo CABG in select cases.', 'text', '{"references": ["PREVENT IV Trial", "ACC CABG Graft Patency Data"]}', '2026-03-16 10:37:00'),
('msg-155', 'conv-006', 'assistant', 'Regarding yoga for Dinesh: I have added a cardiac yoga program referral to his rehab plan. The hospital partners with a certified yoga therapy center that runs a CABG/PCI recovery yoga program. Sessions are Tuesdays and Thursdays at 7 AM. First session is a one-on-one assessment with the yoga therapist. Enrolled him starting April 8.', 'text', NULL, '2026-03-19 09:50:00'),
